<div class="sub-content-header">Palm Pre Wins CNET Best of CES 2009 and People's Voice Award</div>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i><span class="smallText">Jan 12, 2009 12:53:39</span></i>

<br /><br />

<IMG height=192 src="/images/content/CNET_Best_of_CES_09.jpg" width=100 align=right>CNET, in partnership with the <A href="http://www.CE.org" target=_blank>Consumer Electronics Association</A>, handed out its <A href="http://ces.cnet.com/best-of-ces/" target=_blank>Best of CES 2009 Awards</A>, including Best in Show and the People's Voice Award. This year's big winner? The Palm Pre. The Palm Pre smartphone took home both honors and became the first cell phone/smartphone to win the Best in Show since CNET started presenting the Best of CES awards in 2006. CNET News writer Bonnie Cha wasn't kidding when she said Palm was going&nbsp;up against some&nbsp;formidable competitors, including the Sony DSC-G3 and the Sony P-series Lifestyle PC. <BR><BR>In addition to Bestof Show and People's Voice, the <A href="http://ces.cnet.com/best-of-ces/" target=_blank>CNET Best of CES Awards</A> are given in 10 categories. <A href="http://ces.cnet.com/best-of-ces/" target=_blank>See who earned Best of CES 2009 bragging rights.</A><BR><BR>Visit <A href="http://www.cnet.com/ces" target=_blank>www.cnet.com/ces</A> for full coverage of the awards and CES.
