<div class="sub-content-header">Sound From All Directions</div>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i><span class="smallText">Jan 10, 2009 01:25:48</span></i>

<br /><br />

The third day of the International CES brings you the third of four bonus features on the <A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">30 Days of Innovation: A Countdown to CES</A>.<IMG height=173 src="/images/photos/GenAudio_Image.jpg" width=288 align=right><BR><STRONG><BR>Day 1 + 3: GenAudio: Sound from All Directions</STRONG> <BR><BR>Recently named a top three finalist in the CES i-Stage competition, GenAudio will be at CES for the first time this year debuting a new 4D audio technology. This technology enables sound to be perceived as coming from all directions in a 360-degree environment. The first of its kind, a professional version of the technology was recently used to mix the audio for the Hellboy II: The Golden Army DVD and Robin Thicke's latest album, Something Else. The company will be officially launching a consumer version of the technology, called <A href="http://www.astoundsterio.com" target=_blank>AstoundStereo</A>. This enables all existing digital audio on a consumer's computer to be mixed in real-time applying the technology. <A href="http://www.genaudioinc.com" target=_blank>Demo the technology online</A>, and see it live in the LVCC, South Hall, Booth #21853.
