<IMG height=231 hspace=8 src="/images/photos/schwab.jpg" width=300 align=right vspace=5>Dozens of international delegations are busy walking the show floor, meeting with exhibitors and attending receptions at this year’s show. These delegations consist of foreign buyers, manufacturers, press and other CE industry professionals. Most delegations are led by tour operators, U.S. Department of Commerce Foreign Commercial Specialists and other associations such as the National U.S. Arab Chamber of Commerce. Many delegations come from countries that have liberal free trade agreements such as Bahrain and are seeking partners who are seeking to do business in their country. Yesterday, U.S. Ambassador Susan Schwab, welcomed some of the delegations in the South Hall International Commerce Center. Exhibitors, press and attendees who are interested in meeting with these delegations are encouraged to visit the South Hall International Commerce Center. <BR><BR>Meeting with Ambassador Schwab were (from left): Curtis Silvers, Director Government Affairs, National US Arab Chamber of Commerce; Ahmed Al Hujairy, CEO, Gulf Future Business; Randy Innis, Chairman, Nevada District Export Council; Adel Al Safar, Chairman, Alsafar Group, Board Member, Bahrain Chamber of Commerce &amp; Industry and VP, American Chamber of Commerce, Bahrain; Ambassador Susan Schwab, United States Trade Representative; Yousif Almahdi, Co-CEO, Bahrain Chamber of Commerce &amp; Industry; Mazin Al Shehabi, Managing Director, Mazin Computer Center and Chairman, ICT Committee, Bahrain Chamber of Commerce &amp; Industry; and, Rudy N. Vogel, Senior Trade Adviser, IESC.
