The International CES is about innovation. The most important technologies launched at CES, including the VCR, DVD player, HDTVand satellite radio. Why does the average U.S. household have 24 consumer electronics (CE) products?&nbsp; Because they improve our lives, and in times like these, making life good – especially in our homes – is more important than ever.<BR><BR>That's why this year we launched "<A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">30 Days of Innovation: The Countdown to CES</A>," a window into the kind of technological innovation only found at CES. See 30 new CES exhibitors – a new one each day – from among more than 300 companies showing their innovation to CES attendees for the first time. But this is just the beginning. Imagine learning about next-gen technology from 2,700 of the world’s leading companies in one trip.<BR><BR>And with show doors officially opening tomorrow, we find ourselves at <A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">Day One of the countdown</A> with Sendero Group.<BR><BR><IMG height=38 hspace=8 src="/images/content/Sendero_Group_Photo.jpg" width=200 align=right vspace=5>Sendero Group LLC is a pioneer in accessible location information and navigation technologies. Sendero and the National Federation of the Blind will be hosting Stevie Wonder and his technology friends at their booth in the Sands, #72044. You’ll get to meet Stevie Wonder and see products that make the world more accessible to the visually impaired, including the Talking Thermostat from talkingthermostats.com, Apple’s iPod Nano 4th Generation, Atomic Clock by Cobalt, VoiceMe from Humanity Oriented Technology (HOT) and the Nokia N82 cell phone. <BR><BR>See all of these products, along with Sendero’s Best of Innovations 2009 award winning product Code Factory Mobile Geo, the only accessible GPS for blind and visually impaired individuals to run on Windows-Mobile phones and PDAs.<BR><BR>Although the countdown is officially over, we just couldn't stop. New exhibitors and&nbsp;new technology is brimming at CES, so check back each&nbsp;of the four days of the show to see four more featured exhibitors.
