<div class="sub-content-header">Turning Computers into HDTV Channels</div>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i><span class="smallText">Jan 06, 2009 12:19:38</span></i>

<br /><br />

<IMG height=175 hspace=8 src="/images/photos/ZVBox.jpg" width=265 align=left vspace=5>As the <A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">30 Days of Innovation: A Countdown to CES</A> inches forward with just two days to go, we bring you ZeeVee.&nbsp;First-time exhibitor ZeeVee is introducing the ZvBox™ at the 2009 International CES in Las Vegas. The product turns your computer into a high-definition TV channel by “localcasting” over the existing coaxial wiring to all HDTVs in your home. Without cluttering the living room, watch Internet TV, browse the Web and view photos—all from your couch using the system’s ZvRemote, an integrated touchpad that controls the computer’s mouse and desktop interface from up to 150 feet away.<BR><BR>The ZvBox uses what the company calls “ZvCast technology” to let viewers access and transmit any online content to all the HDTVs in their homes. The box connects to the monitor output of a computer producing a new high-definition TV channel that ZeeVee calls Zv. The signal is broadcast on an open TV channel across existing cable wiring where it can be tuned in by any connected HDTV in the home.The ZvBox differs from other methods for watching Internet video on TV because it offers subscription free content access, unaltered HD and SD resolution, and use of existing cable wiring to reach HDTVs without interference or the need for multiple set-top boxes.<BR><BR>ZeeVee’s Deborah Joubert said Zee Vee is the first to launch a product in this space. Apple TV and Netflix limit what you can stream. She said, “No one else does it the way we do. The attendees at CES will be interested in this type of product. It is geared for consumers and people who already use the Internet to watch movies and TV shows. Instead of huddling around the computer, you can see it on the big screen.” She added, “It’s the ultimate video on demand. It’s so awesome.”<BR><BR>Check it out here: LVCC, South Hall 1, Booth #21250.
