<IMG height=204 hspace=8 src="/images/photos/Victorinox_Swiss_Army_Knife.jpg" width=152 align=right vspace=5>The VICTORINOX "Swiss Army Knife" is over 100 years old. This legendary pocket multi-tool was created in a small village in Switzerland. Since then, every army recruit has received this pocket tool marked with a symbolic Swiss cross upon entering the army.<BR><BR>This century old legacy has been extended to&nbsp;technologically advanced SwissFlash USB devices and a&nbsp;wide range of other consumer products, and its hatch marks represent Day 3 of the <A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">30 Days of Innovation: A Countodwn to CES</A>. Victorinox is proud to celebrate its 125th year at the 2009 CES, where they will showcase their most popular timepiece collection:<BR><BR><IMG height=204 hspace=8 src="/images/photos/Victorinox_Swiss_Army_Watch.jpg" width=91 align=left vspace=5>The Chrono Classic gives a modern twist to this classic, time-honored design, featuring two LCD windows that display a variety of functions including a chronograph with a 1/100 of a second accuracy, alarm, countdown, and multi-lingual calendar. You can safely travel to a depth of 100 meters. Simplicity, efficiency and excellence - what else would you expect from the makers of the classic Swiss Army Knife?<BR><BR>Whether you're going swimming, in the army, or traveling the globe, classically styled Swiss Army products will guarantee that you're prepared for whatever venture life may bring! <BR><BR>Check out Swiss Army knives, timepieces, and travel gear at LVCC, South Hall 3, Booth #30365, and see other <A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">new-to-CES exhibitors on the countdown</A>.<BR>
