With only five days left to go on the <A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">30 Days of Innovation: A Countdown to CES</A>, we bring you Huawei Communication.<BR><BR><IMG height=140 hspace=8 src="/images/content/140px-Huawei_Logo.jpg" width=140 align=left vspace=5>A tide of Internet fashion is sweeping throughout the world, shedding light on the innovation of connection device. The rotatable series of Huawei USB Stick, with a rotatable connector replacing a separate cap, has been slimly shaped to match even the thinnest notebook in the world. Compatible with global frequency bands and operation systems, these flexible devices blend trendy designs with high speed surfing promises. Experience rotatable connection, and you will find the world rotating with your charm.<BR><BR><A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-6010777/Huawei-Technologies/Details.aspx" target=_blank>Huawei Communication</A> makes its debut at the 2009 International CES as the world's most successful provider of mobile broadband terminals. In 2008, the mobile broadband products delivered by <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-6010777/Huawei-Technologies/Details.aspx" target=_blank>Huawei Communication</A> reached more than 15 million, and total shipment of all terminals hit 80 million units. ABI's latest report lists Huawei Communication as first place in globally supplying mobile broadband terminals. Huawei Communication is committed to being the best terminal products partner for all operators and has already sold products to 470 operators in 130 countries. Huawei Communication has established partnerships with over 70 percent of the top 50 global telecom operators including world-class operators such as Vodafone, TATA, T-Mobile, China Telecom, BT, AM and Telef&oacute;nica.
