<IMG height=135 hspace=8 src="/images/photos/Dashboard_Devices.jpg" width=200 align=left vspace=5>Dashboard Devices, LLC will premiere at the 2009 CES with ENV™ (Entertainment and Navigation for Vehicles) Systems and is the Day 6 feature on the <A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">30 Days of Innovation: A Countdown to CES</A>, which highlights one new CES exhibitor a day. Dashboard Devices, LLC is a developer and manufacturer of multi-functional computers like navigation, entertainment and Wi-Fi, specifically designed to run in automotive and other environments encompassing low voltage systems. <BR><BR>The ENV is composed of two distinct units, the ENV In-Dash Unit and the ENV-XC Computer. Together these units combine to create a multi-functional system capable of endless entertainment and the ability to navigate wherever you want to go. The Dashboard Devices’ Dual Zone kits create a more personalized driving entertainment experience as it allows passengers to select music, movies and more without disrupting the driver’s GPS navigation system or favorite mp3 melodies. With wireless headphones included you can rock out to your favorite jams or enjoy a quality film without distracting your driver. Dashboard Devices, LLC also creates accessories like a “rear-view camera” and OBDII "Engine Diagnostic System" to access health information for your car. These accessories allow drivers to use the ENV to its optimum capacity and make the ENV both entertaining and practical. <BR><BR>The ENV and other Dashboard Devices will be on display in the Sands Expo Convention Center, Booth #IP211. <BR><BR>Want to know where to see the other companies highlighted on the countdown? <A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">Check the complete list of 30 Days of Innovation.<BR></A>
