<IMG height=63 hspace=8 src="/images/content/ALK_CoPilot.jpg" width=204 align=right>At any given time, we can get in the car, type in an address, and instantly have directions along with an estimated travel time. Thanks to the GPS system, we will never be lost or late again. ALK Technologies is No. 7 on the <A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">30 Days of Innovation: A Countdown to CES</A> and&nbsp;is the company behind award-winning travel and transportation technology such as CoPilot and PC*MILER. ALK, headquartered in Princeton, NJ, was founding in 1979, and strives to use information technology to improve quality of life.
<P>At the 2009 CES, ALK will demonstrate the latest connected GPS navigation innovation: CoPilot Live! COPilot Live is the newest GPS software providing full-featured and connected navigation for a wide range of smart phones! With new colorful 2D and 3D map views, and a step by step address entry ability, finding the way to your destination is as easy as using your phone! Competitions will be held to win the new software, so make sure you visit LVCC, North Hall, Booth #5423. </P>
