<IMG height=175 hspace=8 src="/images/photos/Archerfish_productshot_1208.jpg" width=258 align=left vspace=5>Archerfish by Reston, Va.-based Cernium is the first and only mobile video intelligence (MVI) solution for business owners and homeowners. Debuting at CES, Archerfish gives personal place-shifting technology a home and is our featured exhibitor for Day 8 of the <A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">30 Days of Innovation: A Countdown to CES</A>.<BR><BR>The demands of business and personal life are increasingly complex as people are required to multi-task and juggle multiple roles to achieve a work/life balance. With Archerfish, this balance is made much easier by allowing users to be in more than one place at a time. Based on patented, proven industrial security technology, Archerfish lets users define specific events they wish to be informed of, through a customizable Web portal, which pushes text, picture and video notifications to mobile devices in real-time when a specified event occurs. Where other video systems are passive, Archerfish monitors video and alerts users to situations that require their attention. Archerfish users can be notified of these situations via text message – along with a video clip of the event - to a Web-enabled mobile phone.<BR><BR>Archerfish has been recognized as a 2009 Innovations Design and Engineering Award winner in the Integrated Home Systems product category. During CES, you can find Archerfish in the following places: 
